id2.desc:
A journey to Lake Kel-Suu is an adventure to one of the most fascinating and beautiful spots in Kyrgyzstan. Starting from Bishkek, the route takes you through beautiful valleys, rocky roads and high mountain passes. Along the way, you’ll see amazing views, rushing rivers and wild nature leading to this stunning high-altitude lake.

Located at 3500 meters in the Kok-Kiya Gorge, the lake is known for its rugged shores and bright turquoise waters surrounded by towering cliffs. Here, you can experience complete peace, take walks by the lake and capture incredible photos.

Route Highlights:
• Traveling through mountain passes and thrilling winding roads;
• Staying overnight in yurts or tents in quiet, remote spots by the lake;
• Passing through the natural beauty of Naryn and At-Bashi;
• Spotting wildlife and rare animals along the way.

This route is perfect for adventure lovers who enjoy challenges and want to explore one of Kyrgyzstan’s most remote and breathtaking locations.
